  "summary": "&#34;I am the Bad Wolf. I create myself. I take the words; I scatter them in time and space … a message to lead myself here.&#34; \r<br />Updated in honor of the 12th Doctor&#33;",
  "descriptionHtml": "Lore-Friendly version available&#33;\r<br />\r<br />&#34;I am the Bad Wolf. I create myself. I take the words; I scatter them in time and space … a message to lead myself here.&#34;\r<br />\r<br />This mod serves three purposes:\r<br />The First, to make a Doctor Who joke.\r<br />The Second, to make wolves slightly more awesome.\r<br />The Third, to offer an ongoing quest to gain a familiar-looking amulet.\r<br />\r<br />In my adventures in Skyrim, wolves started out as formidable but became nuisances like Skeevers\r<br />Level 1:\r<br />Wolf: &#34;Grrr I&#39;m a Wolf&#33;&#34;\r<br />Me: &#34;AAAAA Take my money and don&#39;t hurt me&#33;&#34;\r<br />\r<br />Level 42:\r<br />Wolf: &#34;Grrrr I&#39;m a Wolf&#33;&#34;\r<br />Me: &#34;Yeah, that&#39;s great. you&#39;re dead now.&#34;\r<br />\r<br />Level 60:\r<br />Wolf: &#34;Grrr I&#39;m dead now.&#34;\r<br />Me: &#34;Did you hear something, Serana?&#34;\r<br />Serana: &#34;Yes? What&#39;d you need?&#34;\r<br />\r<br />So I thought, &#34;Gee, a leveled wolf would be cool. What would it be called though? Well, duh. Bad Wolf. It HAS to be Bad Wolf. Allons-y&#33;&#34;\r<br />\r<br />The Bad Wolf will always be 80% of your level and want to devour your face, giving you a nice challenge&#33;\r<br />\r<br />[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/36422]Check out my torch wood mod, if you like [/url]\r<br />\r<br />Oh, and I&#39;m playing one of my characters as [url=http://skyrimtimelord.blogspot.com/]A Time Lord in Skyrim[/url]\r<br />\r<br />\r<br />\r<br />\r<br />\r<br />\r<br />\r<br />\r<br />As River Song says, &#34;Spoilers&#33;&#34; \r<br />\r<br />\r<br />\r<br />\r<br />There is a 42% chance that a Bad Wolf will be holding a special key. This key can be used to open the 13 strongboxes scattered throughout Skyrim next to 13 instances of the words &#34;Bad Wolf.&#34; Each strongboxe contains a gem fragment.\r<br />If you can find 12 of the 13 fragments, you can smelt them with a gold or quicksilver ingot into the Two-Heart Amulet, which fortifies your health and healing rate. \r<br />\r<br />\r<br />The Two-Heart amulet is modeled after an object from Doctor Who. As to what it is...well...let&#39;s just say there&#39;s a lot of human nature involved. ;)\r<br />\r<br />Check the forums on this page for the locations of all 13 instances of Bad Wolf, if you&#39;re incredibly impatient. Or, if you are patient, watch this 30 minute video where I show you 11 instances of it, with the help of the Doctor&#39;s Wife:\r<br />\r<br />[youtube]Hx2HvdXia24[/youtube]\r<br />\r<br />And here&#39;s a video explaining the two other locations:\r<br />\r<br />[youtube]hFuBZMKRVYs[/youtube]",
